Package com.ekito.simpleKML.model

Class Summary
AbstractView This is an abstract element and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
Alias contains a mapping from a sourceHref to a targetHref
BaloonStyle Specifies how the description balloon for placemarks is drawn.
Boundary Contains a LinearRing element.
Camera Defines the virtual camera that views the scene.
Change Modifies the values in an element that has already been loaded with a NetworkLink.
ColorStyle This is an abstract element and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
Coordinate A single tuple consisting of floating point values for longitude, latitude, and altitude (in that order).
Coordinates A list of Tuples consisting of floating point values for longitude, latitude, and altitude (in that order).
Create Adds new elements to a Folder or Document that has already been loaded via a NetworkLink.
Data Creates an untyped name/value pair.
Delete This example deletes a Placemark previously loaded into Google Earth.
Document A Document is a container for features and styles.
ExtendedData The ExtendedData element offers three techniques for adding custom data to a KML Feature (NetworkLink, Placemark, GroundOverlay, PhotoOverlay, ScreenOverlay, Document, Folder).
Feature This is an abstract element and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
Folder A Folder is used to arrange other Features hierarchically (Folder, Placemark, NetworkLink, or Overlay).
Geometry This is an abstract element and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
GroundOverlay This element draws an image overlay draped onto the terrain.
HotSpot Specifies the position within the Icon that is "anchored" to the Point specified in the Placemark.
Icon Defines an image associated with an Icon style or overlay.
IconStyle Specifies how icons for point Placemarks are drawn, both in the Places panel and in the 3D viewer of Google Earth.
ImagePyramid For very large images, you'll need to construct an image pyramid, which is a hierarchical set of images, each of which is an increasingly lower resolution version of the original image.
Kml The root element of a KML file.
LabelStyle Specifies how the name of a Feature is drawn in the 3D viewer.
LatLonAltBox A bounding box that describes an area of interest defined by geographic coordinates and altitudes.
LatLonBox Specifies where the top, bottom, right, and left sides of a bounding box for the ground overlay are aligned.
LatLonQuad Allows nonrectangular quadrilateral ground overlays.
LinearRing Defines a closed line string, typically the outer boundary of a Polygon.
LineString Defines a connected set of line segments.
LineStyle Specifies the drawing style (color, color mode, and line width) for all line geometry.
Link Link specifies the location of any of the following: KML files fetched by network links Image files used in any Overlay (the Icon element specifies the image in an Overlay; Icon has the same fields as Link) Model files used in the Model element The file is conditionally loaded and refreshed, depending on the refresh parameters supplied here.
ListStyle Specifies how a Feature is displayed in the list view.
Location Specifies the exact coordinates of the Model's origin in latitude, longitude, and altitude.
Lod Lod is an abbreviation for Level of Detail.
LookAt Defines a virtual camera that is associated with any element derived from Feature.
Model A 3D object described in a COLLADA file (referenced in the Link tag).
MultiGeometry A container for zero or more geometry primitives associated with the same feature.
MultiTrack A multi-track element is used to combine multiple track elements into a single conceptual unit.
NetworkLink References a KML file or KMZ archive on a local or remote network.
NetworkLinkControl Controls the behavior of files fetched by a NetworkLink.
Object This is an abstract base class and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
Option The Class Option.
Orientation Describes rotation of a 3D model's coordinate system to position the object in Google Earth.
Overlay This is an abstract element and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
Pair Defines a key/value pair that maps a mode (normal or highlight) to the predefined styleUrl.
PhotoOverlay The PhotoOverlay element allows you to geographically locate a photograph on the Earth and to specify viewing parameters for this PhotoOverlay.
Placemark A Placemark is a Feature with associated Geometry.
Point A geographic location defined by longitude, latitude, and (optional) altitude.
Polygon A Polygon is defined by an outer boundary and 0 or more inner boundaries.
PolyStyle Specifies the drawing style for all polygons, including polygon extrusions (which look like the walls of buildings) and line extrusions (which look like solid fences).
Region A region contains a bounding box (LatLonAltBox) that describes an area of interest defined by geographic coordinates and altitudes.
ResourceMap Specifies 0 or more Alias elements, each of which is a mapping for the texture file path from the original Collada file to the KML or KMZ file that contains the Model.
Scale Scales a model along the x, y, and z axes in the model's coordinate space.
Schema Specifies a custom KML schema that is used to add custom data to KML Features.
SchemaData This element is used in conjunction with Schema to add typed custom data to a KML Feature.
ScreenOverlay This element draws an image overlay fixed to the screen.
SimpleData This element assigns a value to the custom data field identified by the name attribute.
SimpleField The declaration of the custom field, which must specify both the type and the name of this field.
Style A Style defines an addressable style group that can be referenced by StyleMaps and Features.
StyleMap A StyleMap maps between two different Styles.
StyleSelector This is an abstract element and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
TimePrimitive This is an abstract element and cannot be used directly in a KML file.
TimeSpan Represents an extent in time bounded by begin and end dateTimes.
TimeStamp Represents a single moment in time.
Track A track describes how an object moves through the world over a given time period.
Update Specifies an addition, change, or deletion to KML data that has already been loaded using the specified URL.
UpdateProcess Base class for Change, Create and Delete
ViewerOptions This element enables special viewing modes in Google Earth 6.0 and later.
ViewVolume Defines how much of the current scene is visible.
